      {
        "id": "cjgGr04gU0RCeZXfLB25",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Welcome to the SeismicML Mini Activity!</strong></p><p>This first round of development produced two new CLUE tiles, the WaveRunner tile and the Timeline tile. In the WaveRunner tile, users choose which seismic data to visualize by selecting a seismic station and a date range. Users can also use this tile to run the ML model to identify seismic events. With the Timeline tile, users can visualize the seismic data and navigate through it by panning and zooming. The Timeline tile also shows labeled events identified by the ML model in the WaveRunner tile. </p><p>This activity will serve as a quick proof of concept test for the WaveRunner and Timeline tiles in CLUE, as well as for the activities we would hope to do with students during the full SeismicML curriculum.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "drPmXkRDGy0BjBK3",
